                <div class="gb-content-wrapper gb-text-center">
                    <p class="gb-text-large">
                        Most of us don’t think about it, but the DNS (Domain Name System) is
                        used each day by everyone on the Internet to look up websites. The
                        DNS runs the Internet, living in the background, making all the
                        connections you need to run a website. But everything the DNS does
                        is time-limited. If a connection request takes too long, it will
                        simply drop the request.
                    </p>
